<p>I am trying to use Data binding. It is work properly if I use object that has attribute of string, but in this case I use int and it doesn't work. I have object User:</p>  <pre><code>public class User extends BaseObservable{         public int age;         ......           public User() {}          public int getAge() {             return age;         }          public void setAge(int age) {             this.age = age;         }          ...      } </code></pre>  <p>here is my layout</p>  <pre><code>&lt;?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?&gt; &lt;layout xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"&gt;     &lt;data&gt;         &lt;variable name="user" type="com.example.bindingview.User"/&gt;     &lt;/data&gt;     &lt;LinearLayout         android:orientation="vertical"         android:layout_width="match_parent"         android:layout_height="match_parent"&gt;          &lt;TextView             android:layout_width="match_parent"             android:layout_height="wrap_content"             android:text="@{user.age}"/&gt;     &lt;/LinearLayout&gt; &lt;/layout&gt; </code></pre>  <p>The problem is that TextView cannot have text of age that is int. if I change from int to string of age attribute it worked fine. What should I do to avoid this problem?</p>